data:
The T stage is determined by the size of the primary tumor.
T1 tumors are 2.0 cm or less in size.
T2 tumors are between 2.1 to 5.0 cm in size.
T3 tumors are larger than 5.0 cm in size or have grown into the chest wall.
T4 tumors have grown into the skin or chest wall, or have developed into inflammatory carcinoma.

T stage is not affected by the presence or absence of tumor in the sentinel lymph nodes.
